Comparison of models

We can make a check between model 3 and 4 to make sure there is no difference. As expected there isnt a significant difference between the two models. So we keep the simpler, optimal model 4. And base the rest of the analysis on this model.

Dilemma

Here we are confronted with a dilemma. Ive included Net Payer, because it generates a result. However, if I include, say CP per capita, then you dont get a result.

In short, if we want an additional, significant interaction then we should go with model 4 and Net Payer. Alternatively, the Annex below shows the regression outputs if we include a numeric version (in this case CP per capita). Note variables have to be standardised; its the (scale) function in the formula.

Summary

It seems that optimal model 4 is the way to go. Slightly more of a story to tell there. Well need to tidy up the regression output and plots, but thats relatively straightforward.
